*.local.toml
*.env

# Caches
[Cc]ache/
.[Cc]ache/

# masking-pin-lint cache is intentionally tracked: D11 in
# specs/006-engine-rule-refactor/decisions.md requires daily-refreshed
# cache files committed to the repo so CI's cache-with-fallback path has
# data even when GitHub's API is unreachable. The negation below carves
# that directory out of the generic [Cc]ache/ rule above.
!tools/masking-pin-lint/cache/
!tools/masking-pin-lint/cache/**

# proptest persistent failure seeds are intentionally tracked. Each
# `*.proptest-regressions` file carries the seed of a real property-test
# failure proptest discovered locally; checking them in makes the seed
# part of CI so the same input is re-tried before any new shrink work,
# permanently locking in the regression. Adding `*.proptest-regressions`
# to .gitignore would silently un-track these and reopen the regression
# window. Issue #704 (P3 monotonicity violation in CAPCO closure) is the
# motivating instance: the failing seed `cc e88bf36f...` was untracked
# at discovery; once the proptest-regressions file landed in CI, the
# fix's correctness became permanently regression-tested. REUSE.toml
# carries an explicit `**/*.proptest-regressions` annotation that names
# the license directly so a future narrowing of the `tests/**` bulk
# block cannot silently strip license coverage from these files.
# Do NOT add `*.proptest-regressions` to this file.

# Python bytecode (tools/perf/ utilities are Python; users running
# them locally create __pycache__/ directories).
__pycache__/
*.pyc

